[p 
	"Despite Tails having the ability to fly around obstacles, he can only fly but so far and for only a certain length in time so I had to take a slight change in direction to get to the spring sooner. Mecha Knuckles was a nightmare! I've actually had given up on the TAS a time or two because of him... Sadly, I couldn't get any better results than this.
	$LF
]p
[h4 id=EggRocket1-(displayedas4:27:08ingame) 
	" Egg Rocket 1 - (displayed as 4:27:08 in game)
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"Ohh Egg Rocket, how I still and forever will hate you so! This run made use of a glitch that pushes Tails through the floor and causes the level to lose solidarity. Thus making it possible to complete it in one go. A route change was made here as well, which made it possible to complete it even faster than the Knuckles run.
	$LF
]p
[h4 id=CosmicAngel2-1:02:97 
	" Cosmic Angel 2 - 1:02:97
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"This one was a doozy. Unlike Knuckles, who can easily gain high speed through the half way point of the act, Tails has to maintain speed differently. The boss fight was mostly intentional self-damaging to hit the boss sooner during Tails' invincibility frames.
	$LF
]p
